You‚Äôre getting this error because --add-exports is not supported in Java 8.
That option was introduced in Java 9 with the module system (Project Jigsaw).

Since you‚Äôre running Maven with Zulu-8 (Java 8):

C:\Program Files\Zulu\zulu-8\bin\java.exe

Java 8 simply doesn‚Äôt recognize:

--add-exports java.base/sun.nio.ch=ALL-UNNAMED

‚úî Why you see the error

Java 8 ‚Üí ‚ùå does not support --add-exports
Java 9+ ‚Üí ‚úî supports --add-exports

So the JVM exits before Maven can start.

‚∏ª

‚úÖ How to fix it

Option 1 ‚Äî Remove the --add-exports line (if you don‚Äôt need it for Java 8)

Since Java 8 does not enforce module access, you can normally access sun.nio.ch without exports.

So your JVM config could simply be:

-Djavax.net.ssl.trustStoreType=Windows-ROOT


‚∏ª

Option 2 ‚Äî Switch Maven to run with Java 9+ (if you actually need --add-exports)

Keep your project using Java 8 for compilation, but run Maven with Java 11 or Java 17.

In IntelliJ:

Settings ‚Üí Build Tools ‚Üí Maven ‚Üí JDK
Select a JDK ‚â• 11.

Or using environment variables:

set JAVA_HOME=C:\Program Files\Zulu\zulu-17

Then run Maven again.

‚∏ª

Option 3 ‚Äî Disable IntelliJ from injecting that JVM argument

If IntelliJ added it automatically:
	1.	Go to:
Help ‚Üí Edit Custom VM Options
	2.	Remove the line:

--add-exports java.base/sun.nio.ch=ALL-UNNAMED


	3.	Restart IntelliJ.

‚∏ª

